result.execSummary:
The defendant Dusten W. Kalakay was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dusten W. Kalakay is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant, Dusten W. Kalakay appeared with Attorney James C. McLaughlin.  Attorney Thomas H Frost appeared for the State.  Also has 14 CM 201.  State recites plea agreement defendant will plead to 14 CM 201 and count 2 in 14 CF 138 - probation 3 years with 5 Mo in custody concurrent.  Atty McL agrees.  Court questions defendant re: plea questionnaire.  Court questions the repeater allegation - state will keep that on and Atty McL will accept it.  Court continues to address the defendant.  Defendant entered plea of nc to count 2 in 14 CF 138 and 14 CM 201.  Court finds defendant guilty count 2 in 14 CF 138 and 14 CM 201 and count 1 in 14 CF 138 is dismissed.  State argues sentencing.  Atty McL argues sentencing.

COURT:  Sentence w/held probation 3 years - costs as to both counts - 5 months county jail on both counts to run concurrent to each other credit for 10 days time served  with huber to begin on/before 2/27/15 by 4 PM - undergo any counciling recommended - successfully complete cognitive behavior program  - no contact with Ashley Parker
